'''Elisabeth Berge''' (born 27 November 1954) is a Norwegian businessperson and civil servant.

She graduated with the [[siviløkonom|siv.øk.]] degree from the [[Norwegian School of Economics and Business Administration]] in 1978, and as Master of Arts in Economics from the [[University of California]] in 1979. She worked in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Petroleum and Energy|Ministry of Petroleum and Energy]] from 1981 to 1990, since 1986 as a deputy under-secretary of State. She then worked in [[Statoil]] from 1990 to 2004, since 2001 as chief of communications. In 2004 she was appointed permanent under-secretary of State in the Ministry of Petroleum and Energy.<ref name=hvem>{{cite book |title=Hvem er hvem?|chapter=Berge, Elisabeth|year=2008|editor=[[Knut Olav Åmås|Åmås, Knut Olav]] |publisher=Aschehoug |location=Oslo |isbn=978-82-03-23561-0|page=53}}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Elisabeth Berge|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Elisabeth_Berge|language=Norwegian|accessdate=17 February 2011}}</ref>

She was a member of the board of [[Statnett]] from 1992 to 2000 and the [[Kavli Trust|Kavli Foundation]] from 1999 to 2004.<ref name=hvem/>

