{{Infobox Politician | name = Everard Daigle | image = | caption = |birth_name= | birth_date ={{birth date and age|1925|12|2}} | birth_place =[[Saint-Léonard, New Brunswick]] | death_date= | death_place= | office = [[Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick|MLA]] for [[Victoria-la-Vallée|Grand Falls]] | term=1974–1987 | predecessor= | successor=[[Paul Duffie]] | party = [[New Brunswick Liberal Association]] | religion = | profession = | occupation = Businessman | spouse = Jeannette Dionne (m. 1948) | children = | residence = }} '''Everard H. Daigle''' (born December 2, 1925) is a Canadian politician. He served in the [[Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick]] from 1974 to 1987, as a Liberal member for the constituency of Grand Falls.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=xkmIAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Daigle,+Everard%22+grand+falls&dq=%22Daigle,+Everard%22+grand+falls&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CB4Q6AEwAGoVChMIrMLawLHcyAIVTJqICh2sMgyC|title=Guide Parlementaire Canadien|first=Pierre G.|last=Normandin|date=20 January 1985|publisher=Gale Canada|via=Google Books}}</ref>
