'''Ingeborg Moen Borgerud''' (born {{birth date|1949|09|23|df=y}}) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[lawyer]], businessperson and former politician for the [[Norwegian Labour Party|Labour Party]].

==Career==
She was born in [[Porsgrunn]]. In her early career she worked in [[Akershus County Municipality]], the [[Norwegian Ministry of Justice and the Police]], Oslo Probate Court, and under the [[Norwegian Parliamentary Ombudsman for Public Administration|Norwegian Parliamentary Ombudsman]]. She then became deputy leader of the judicial department in the [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions]].<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=Fire nye statssekretærer|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=18 September 1992|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In September 1992, she was appointed [[State Secretary (Norway)|State Secretary]] in the Ministry of Justice and the Police, in [[Brundtland's Third Cabinet]]. She remained here until 1996.<ref name=ntb/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.regjeringen.no/en/the-government/previous-governments/the-structure-of-the-registry/ministries-and-offices/government-secretariats-and-ministries-s/ministries-since-1814/ministry-of-justice-and-the-police/ministry-of-justice-and-the-police-state.html?id=440614|title=Norwegian Ministry of Justice and the Police. State Secretaries|publisher=[[Government.no]]|accessdate=18 November 2010}}</ref>

She held several public posts. In 1987 she was named as a member of ''Klagenemnda for likestilling''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Offisielt fra statsråd|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=22 May 1987|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She was the deputy chair of the [[Norwegian Banks' Guarantee Fund|Norwegian Savings Banks' Guarantee Fund]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Våre nye bankledere|last=Elsrud|first=Sigrid|date=6 January 1992|work=Aftenposten|page=34|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She has contributed to public committees that produce [[Norwegian Official Report]]s. She chaired the committees that delivered the Norwegian Official Report 2003:2 on discrimination and 2004:5 on the working environment.<ref>[http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/fad/dok/nouer/2003/nou-2003-2/2.html?id=118238 NOU 2003: 2], [http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/fad/dok/nouer/2004/nou-2004-5/2.html?id=384821 NOU 2004: 5]</ref> The Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions lambasted her committee's report on the working environment as being hostile to common workers.<ref>{{cite news |title=LO: – Forslaget til arbeidslivslov gufs fra fortida  | url = 
http://www.aftenposten.no/jobb/article736103.ece| agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=20 February 2004 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> She was also a member of the committees that delivered the Norwegian Official Report 1994:19 about banking and finance, and 1994:20 (about personal injury compensation, 2001:32 (about civil trials and 2001:33 about arbitration, the committee was named in 1999).<ref>[http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/jd/dok/nouer/1994/nou-1994-19/3.html?id=139647 NOU 1994: 19], [http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/jd/dok/nouer/1994/nou-1994-20/3.html?id=374292 NOU 1994: 20], [http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/jd/dok/nouer/2001/nou-2001-32/3.html?id=378582 NOU 2001: 32], [http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/jd/dok/nouer/2001/nou-2001-33/3.html?id=145107 NOU 2001: 33]</ref> She is also a member of the Quarantine Committee, which works with quarantines between a person's active career in politics and a new career in other sectors.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ekspolitikere avgjør|last=Larsen|first=Christiane Jordheim|date=4 November 2009|work=Klassekampen|page=4|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

She became a deputy board member of the [[Norwegian State Railways]] in October 2000.<ref name=nsb>{{cite news|title=Moen Borgerud ny styreleder i NSB|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=9 February 2004|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She advanced to deputy chair in June 2001, when [[Gunn Wærsted]] left the board.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ingeborg Moen Borgerud ny nestleder i NSB-styret|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=22 June 2001|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In September 2003 she advanced to acting chair when [[Olav Fjell]] left the board.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fjell: – Naturlig å gå også fra NSB|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=23 September 2003|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In February 2004, she began work on the extraordinary stockholders' congress.<ref name=nsb/> She was also the chair of the [[Norwegian National Courts Administration]] for many years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Domstolene holder ikke fristene|last=Svensvik|first=Håvard|date=14 April 2005|work=Stavanger Aftenblad|page=7|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She became a board member of [[Norsk Eiendomsinformasjon]] in 2006,<ref>{{cite news|title=Tar tilbake makta i styrene|last=Hegvik|first=Gunn Kari|date=8 August 2006|work=Dagbladet|page=14|language=Norwegian}}</ref> and chair of [[Eidsiva Energi]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fakta om pengegavene til Senterpartiet|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=6 October 2010|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

As a lawyer, she works in the company Arntzen de Besche. She was the lawyer of [[Ingunn Yssen]] during the [[Valla scandal]] in 2007.<ref>{{cite news|title=Strid om etterlønn til Yssen|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=18 December 2007|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She also represented one of the paramedics in the [[Ambulance controversy (Oslo)|Ali Farah case]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Slipper med refs
|last=Holm|first=Per Annar|date=7 February 2008|work=Aftenposten|page=3|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In 2007, she co-wrote the book ''Arbeidsrett. Særlig om omstilling i offentlig sektor'', released on [[Universitetsforlaget]].<ref>[http://ask.bibsys.no/ask/action/show?pid=060472669&kid=biblio Entry] for ''Arbeidsrett. Særlig om omstilling i offentlig sektor'' in [[BIBSYS]]</ref>

