{{Infobox person |name = John Dorrance III |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |71|2015|11|07}}<ref name=Forbes /> |birth_place = US |death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |death_place = |residence = [[Dublin]], Ireland |nationality = Irish |ethnicity = |citizenship = |other_names = |known_for = [[Campbell's Soup]] heir |education = |alma_mater = |occupation = |years_active = |home_town = |salary = |networth = US$2.6 [[billion]] (November 2015)<ref name=Forbes /> |title = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |boards = |religion = |spouse = married |partner = |children = 2 sons |parents = John T. "Jack" Dorrance Jr |relations = [[John Thompson Dorrance]] (grandfather) |website = }}
'''John Dorrance III''' (born 1943/1944) is an American-born Irish [[billionaire]] businessman and [[Campbell's Soup]] heir. He is also known as "Ippy" Dorrance.
==Early life== He is the son of John T. "Jack" Dorrance Jr. (1919–1989), and grandson of [[John Thompson Dorrance]].<ref name=Forbes /><ref name=PhiladelphiaInquirer />
==Career== As of November 2015, ''[[Forbes]]'' estimated his net worth at US$2.6 billion.<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=John Dorrance III.|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/john-dorrance-iii/|website=Forbes|accessdate=7 November 2015}}</ref>
==Personal life== For 15 years he lived on a ranch in [[Wyoming]], before moving to Ireland. ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'' reported that, "In Ireland, he can pay half the 30 percent U.S. tax rate on dividends, and when he dies, his estate will be taxed at 35 percent, rather than 55 percent in the United States."<ref name=PhiladelphiaInquirer>{{cite news|last1=Warner|first1=Susan|title=Heir Sells 14 Percent Of Stake In Campbell John T. Dorrance 3d Was A Staunch Supporter Of Family Control. Now, He's Sold At Least $244 Million Worth Of Shares.|url=http://articles.philly.com/1996-09-21/news/25632332_1_dorrance-family-campbell-shares-campbell-soup|accessdate=8 November 2015|work=The Philadelphia Inquirer|date=September 21, 1996}}</ref>
He is married with two children and lives in Dublin.<ref name=Forbes />
