'''Raad Ghantous''' (born in [[Baghdad]], [[Iraq]])<ref name=coastalmagazine>{{cite web | url =http://www.coastmagazine.com/archive/pre_dec05/feature/8.05_f3.html | title =coast magazine | accessdate =2007-08-24 | publisher =coastmagazine.com |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070403173125/http://www.coastmagazine.com/archive/pre_dec05/feature/8.05_f3.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-04-03}}</ref> is an [[interior designer]] who was involved in the redesigning of the Cultural Center in [[San Clemente]].
== Early life == His mother was half [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]] and half [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]], of the [[Chaldean Catholic]] church.<ref name=journal>{{cite web | url =http://www.sanclementejournal.com/pastissues/2004/2004_01/sanclementean.htm | title =Raad:Journal | accessdate =2007-08-24 | publisher =sanclementejournal.com | deadurl =yes | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070927025640/http://www.sanclementejournal.com/pastissues/2004/2004_01/sanclementean.htm | archivedate =2007-09-27 | df = }}</ref><ref name=coastalmagazine>{{cite web | url =http://www.coastmagazine.com/archive/pre_dec05/feature/8.05_f3.html | title =coast magazine | accessdate =2007-08-24 | publisher =coastmagazine.com |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070403173125/http://www.coastmagazine.com/archive/pre_dec05/feature/8.05_f3.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-04-03}}</ref> His father was an [[Eastern Orthodox]] [[civil engineer]], he was born in Iraq.<ref name=coastalmagazine>{{cite web | url =http://www.coastmagazine.com/archive/pre_dec05/feature/8.05_f3.html | title =coast magazine | accessdate =2007-08-24 | publisher =coastmagazine.com |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070403173125/http://www.coastmagazine.com/archive/pre_dec05/feature/8.05_f3.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-04-03}}</ref> His grandfather moved to Iraq from [[Haifa]], (then in [[Mandatory Palestine]]) because of the educational facilities available in Iraq, later on his father and the family moved to [[Abu Dhabi]] but didn't settle as they left for [[Kuwait]], where Raad had attended high school and then he received a degree in economics at the [[American College of Switzerland]] in [[Leysin]].
He later on sought refuge in the [[United States]], where he decided to undertake a course in interior design and received his degree.<ref name=journal>{{cite web | url =http://www.sanclementejournal.com/pastissues/2004/2004_01/sanclementean.htm | title =Raad:Journal | accessdate =2007-08-24 | publisher =sanclementejournal.com | deadurl =yes | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070927025640/http://www.sanclementejournal.com/pastissues/2004/2004_01/sanclementean.htm | archivedate =2007-09-27 | df = }}</ref>
==Career== He soon landed a job for Whimberly Allison, Tong & Go and has also worked for [[Hirsch Bedner Associates|Hirsch-Bedner]] and Design 1. He has designed many projects such as a mansion in Beverly Hills, his work has proven successful and rewarding as the location of most of his projects are in exotic places such as [[Spain]], [[China]], [[Japan]] and the [[United Arab Emirates]]. He soon started his own interior business, Raad Ghantous & Associates, in which he imports accessories from [[Morocco]] and [[Egypt]] to accompany his work.<ref name=journal>{{cite web | url =http://www.sanclementejournal.com/pastissues/2004/2004_01/sanclementean.htm | title =Raad:Journal | accessdate =2007-08-24 | publisher =sanclementejournal.com | deadurl =yes | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070927025640/http://www.sanclementejournal.com/pastissues/2004/2004_01/sanclementean.htm | archivedate =2007-09-27 | df = }}</ref>
He currently{{when|date=February 2016}} serves on the Design Committee in the LA Downtown Business Association.{{citation needed|date=February 2016}}
